---
title: "CodeBlock Component"
---

# CodeBlock

A styled code block for displaying source code with syntax highlighting, an optional language label, and a copy-to-clipboard button. Code is highlighted at build time with Shiki. The copy button uses Preact for client-side hydration.

## Properties

| Property | Type | Default | Description |
|----------|------|---------|-------------|
| `content` | `string` | — | The code content to display (provided automatically by fenced code blocks) |
| `language` | `string` | — | Language identifier shown as a label in the header |

## Examples

### Without language

```
This is a plain code block
with no language specified.
```

### JavaScript

```javascript
const greeting = "Hello, world!";
console.log(greeting);
```

### Python

```python
def greet(name: str) -> str:
    return f"Hello, {name}!"
```

### Markdoc

```markdoc
{% alert type="info" %}
This is an informational alert.
{% /alert %}
```
